paragraphs.title: Import the node and edge data

%python
import pandas as pd

edges = pd.read_csv('/usr/zeppelin/notebook/data/edge - 01-31-2017.csv')
edges['OriginCode'] = edges['OriginCode'].str.strip()
edges['DestinationCode'] = edges['DestinationCode'].str.strip()
edges['CustomerCode'] = edges['CustomerCode'].str.strip()
edges['CustomerSalesRep'] = edges['CustomerSalesRep'].str.strip()
edges['CustomerName'] = edges['CustomerName'].str.strip()



nodes = pd.read_csv('/usr/zeppelin/notebook/data/node - 02-01-2017.txt', sep = '|')
nodes['CompanyCode'] = nodes['CompanyCode'].str.strip()


###clean up only matching ones for edges and nodes in terms of Wcode
nodes = nodes.loc[nodes['CompanyCode'].isin(edges['OriginCode']) | nodes['CompanyCode'].isin(edges['DestinationCode']) ]

print("Nodes first 5")
nodes.head()
print("Edges first 5")
edges.head()

paragraphs.title: Prepare The List of Customer Specific Data
paragraphs.text:
%python
import networkx as nx
edgesGB = pd.DataFrame(edges.groupby(['OriginCode','DestinationCode','CustomerName']).size().rename('counts'))
edgesGB = pd.DataFrame(edgesGB.to_records())
Graph = nx.DiGraph()
Graph.add_edges_from([(d[0],d[1],dict(weight=d[3],CustomerName=d[2])) for d in
                         edgesGB[['OriginCode','DestinationCode','CustomerName','counts']].values])

# add on node properties for Customer Name
nodeCustomer = nodes.set_index('CompanyCode')['Name']
nx.set_node_attributes(Graph, 'Name', nodeCustomer)

paragraphs.title: Clean up Nodes without a Name Attribute
paragraphs.text:
%python
hasLabel = list((n for n in Graph if 'Name' in Graph.node[n]))
SubGraph = Graph.subgraph(hasLabel)

paragraphs.title: Pick off the Nodes with Target Customer and all Edges into Target Warehouses + Nearest Node Distrubution
paragraphs.text:
%python
TargetCustomer = 'CDW'
CustomerWarehouses = [n for n in SubGraph if SubGraph.node[n]['Name'] == TargetCustomer]
print("First 10 Customer Warehouses ")
CustomerWarehouses[0:9]

###Clip the graph to only the nodes
print("First 10 GraphCut of all unique inbound and outbound neighboring nodes that are not in the customer warehouse")
l = [list(nx.all_neighbors(SubGraph,n)) for n in CustomerWarehouses]
AllNeighbors = list(set([item for sublist in l for item in sublist if item not in CustomerWarehouses]))
AllNeighbors[0:9]
len(AllNeighbors)

###Take all nodes in any direction
EdgesWarehouses = [(u,v,d) for u,v,d in SubGraph.edges_iter(data=True) if (v in CustomerWarehouses) or (u in CustomerWarehouses)]
print("First 10 of All edges in any direction")
EdgesWarehouses[0:9]
len(EdgesWarehouses)

###Select only inbound edges to the customer and the warehouses that the freight came from and eliminate internal moves
EdgesWarehouses = [(u,v,d) for u,v,d in SubGraph.edges_iter(data=True) if (v in CustomerWarehouses) and (u not in CustomerWarehouses)]
print("First 10 Edges that are inbound to all customer Warehouses and not internal moves")
EdgesWarehouses[0:9]
len(EdgesWarehouses)

###These are the adjacent warehouses (nearest neighbors) we are interested in modeling 
print("First 10 adjacent warehouses")
AdjacentWarehouses = [u for u,v,d in EdgesWarehouses if u not in CustomerWarehouses]
AdjacentWarehouses[0:9]
len(AdjacentWarehouses)

###This is the edge network for those adjacent warehouses that do not connect to the target customer (either direction)
print("First 10 Adjacent Edges of the Target Warehouse Network Not Connected to Customer Target")
AdjacentWarehouseEdges = [(u,v,d) for u,v,d in SubGraph.edges_iter(data=True) if ((v in AdjacentWarehouses) or (u in AdjacentWarehouses)) and ((v not in CustomerWarehouses) and (u not in CustomerWarehouses))]
AdjacentWarehouseEdges[0:9]
len(AdjacentWarehouseEdges)

###Now We Generate the Network Graph
WarehouseNetworkX = nx.DiGraph()
WarehouseNetworkX.add_edges_from(AdjacentWarehouseEdges)
WarehouseNetworkX.add_edges_from(EdgesWarehouses)
nx.info(WarehouseNetworkX)

paragraphs.title: Now We Collapse the Network Into A Central Customer Node (Put all Red into One And Get Customer Distribution)
paragraphs.text:
%python
###Make the Compressed NetworkX Graph
edgesTMP = [((u,TargetCustomer,d) if v in CustomerWarehouses else (u,v,d)) for u,v,d in WarehouseNetworkX.edges_iter(data=True)]
collapsedNX = nx.DiGraph()
collapsedNX.add_edges_from(edgesTMP)

G = nx.Graph()
G.add_edges_from(collapsedNX.edges_iter(), weight=0)

for u, v, d in collapsedNX.edges_iter(data=True):
    G[u][v]['weight'] += d['weight']
    G[u][v]['CustomerName'] = d['CustomerName']


for u, v, d in G.edges_iter(data=True):
    G[u][v]['CustomerName'] = d['CustomerName'] + ":" + str(d['weight'])

print(nx.info(G))


print("First 10 edges")
G.edges(data=True)[0:9]

kv = {n:("red" if n in TargetCustomer else "blue") for n in G}
nx.set_node_attributes(G,"color",kv)

print("First 10 colored nodes")
G.nodes(data=True)[0:9]

###construct the node labels
labels = {node:node for node in G.nodes() if node in TargetCustomer}
edgelabels = nx.get_edge_attributes(G,'CustomerName')
edgelabels = {k:v for k,v in edgelabels.items() if (k[0] in TargetCustomer) or (k[1] in TargetCustomer)}
